snippet.title: How to 3 Flip (or Die)
snippet.description:
Get Skateboard Gear at My Skateshop - http://www.theshredquarters.com

Subscribe for more skateboarding, skits, and randomness! Ok I taught this one, assuming you have some experience with flip tricks already. But here are some quick pointers!

1. If you're having problem landing on top of your board watch my Hot to Kickflip video, you have to train yourself to jump up, over your board!

2. Like I said in the video, the spin is hard to get used to. So sweep your back foot hard and use your front foot to help push the board as you flick, Essentially doing a scissor kick motion.

3. It took me months to learn this trick, partly because I started trying to learn it immediately when I started skating. But don't get discouraged if it takes long. It may take some real time and effort, but if you try hard and long enough, you'll get it eventually!

4. Sugar gliders are adorable.

snippet.title: How To Double Kickflip (or Die!)
snippet.description:
Subscribe for more videos!
Facebook - http://www.facebook.com/officialandyschrock
Instagram - @AndySchrock
Twitter - @AndySchrock

Here's my newest how to video! I hope this helps anyone who is having trouble with it. One thing I want to stress is that once you get the hang of flipping double flips, it will make the flip trick look better if you get used to doing the trick without pulling your foot back so much. But for learning, pulling your foot back definitely helps out a lot. The further you pull your foot back the more rocket-esque your flip will be. So after you learn it, make leveling it out your next step and moving your foot back up will help you with that. Hope that makes sense to you guys!

I'll be doing more how to vids so be on the lookout. Take it easy info readers!

snippet.title: Did This Alchemist Predict the Atomic Bomb? | Fulcanelli
snippet.description:
Alchemy is a mystifying art with a deep and rich history, with many practitioners throughout the centuries. One of those practitioners is said to have found the Philosophers Stone, the secret to immortality. What makes this all the more spectacular is that this person existed less than a hundred years ago, but his identity remains unknown. Today we look into the identity of who is perhaps the most mysterious person in history, the Last Alchemist Fulcanelli.

Sam Witwer (Being Human, Star Wars) joins us this week and we get deep. He opens up about reassessing his life and how peoples impression of him being a screw up molded his self image for years. 

Sam talks about how this industry encourages people to hide vulnerability and put up a front; and how some of the false fame that can come as a side effect of this can be harmful to your mental health. 

Whole lot of real life talk in this episode, but we also get into Sams love for (and career with) the Star Wars franchise, how some of the SiFi issues resolved on Being Human, and his experience in Season 8 of Smallville.
